Aurora Core is a client-side runtime kernel built on HTML5.
It executes entirely in the browser with zero dependencies,
zero setup, and full local reproducibility.

The kernel stabilizes a dynamic lightfield and exposes an
emergent structure without relying on external systems,
servers, or APIs. Aurora Core is fully portable and can be
deployed by simple copy–paste.

This repository provides the minimal source required to run
the Aurora Core and demonstrate its runtime behavior as a
self-contained operator.
